# Meshtastic Firmware Environment Variables - Sample Configuration
# =================================================================
#
# SECURITY WARNING: The default credentials in this firmware are INSECURE!
# You MUST change them before deploying your device in any real network.
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: `cp .env.sample .env`
# 2. Edit the .env file with your secure credentials
# 3. The .env file is automatically excluded from git for security
# 4. Rebuild and flash your firmware after making changes
#
# HOW TO GENERATE SECURE CREDENTIALS:
# - Use a password manager to generate strong, random passwords
# - MQTT username: 8-16 characters, alphanumeric + symbols
# - MQTT password: 16-32 characters, random string
# - WiFi SSID: Your actual network name
# - WiFi PSK: Your actual WiFi password (WPA2 recommended)
#
# =================================================================

# MQTT Configuration
# ==================
# These connect your device to the Meshtastic MQTT network for remote monitoring
# Default (INSECURE): username="meshdev", password="large4cats"
#
# Replace with your own secure credentials:
MQTT_USERNAME=your_unique_mqtt_username_here
MQTT_PASSWORD=your_strong_mqtt_password_here

# WiFi Configuration
# ==================
# These allow your device to connect to WiFi for internet bridging
# Default (INSECURE): ssid="wifi_ssid", password="wifi_psk"
#
# Replace with your actual WiFi network credentials:
WIFI_SSID=Your_WiFi_Network_Name
WIFI_PSK=Your_WiFi_Password_Here

# =================================================================
# ADVANCED CONFIGURATION
# =================================================================
#
# The userPrefs.jsonc file references these environment variables.
# After updating .env, rebuild the firmware:
#
#   ./flash_meshtastic.sh
#
# Or manually:
#   pio run -e heltec-v1    # for V1 boards (4MB)
#   pio run -e heltec-v2_1  # for V2/V2.1 boards (8MB)
#
# =================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# =================================================================
#
# ✅ DO:
# - Use unique, randomly generated passwords
# - Use WPA2 or WPA3 WiFi encryption
# - Change credentials before field deployment
# - Keep your .env file private (it's gitignored)
# - Use a password manager for credential storage
#
# ❌ DON'T:
# - Use default passwords in production
# - Share your .env file with others
# - Use easily guessable passwords
# - Commit .env files to version control
# - Use the same password across multiple devices
#
